Package: gspy
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Forensic goroutine-to-syscall inspector for live Go processes
 gspy is a security tool designed for forensics and live malware analysis
 of Go-based binaries. It uses eBPF to hook into the Go runtime and track
 the relationship between internal goroutines and kernel syscalls.
 .
 Key features:
  - Zero ptrace(ATTACH) overhead.
  - Multi-architecture support (x86_64, ARM64).
  - Live filtering by networking, I/O, and syscall type.
